column5: Decent movie about the troubles of real-estate agents.
I've never seen it. I keep meaning to but never remember to pick it up when I'm getting a movie.  Tonight there was curling on so I had to pass.  JF
This ones in my top 5 of all time list.
Love the movie, an absolute fantastic cast.  Jack Lemmon's character is timeless.  If you haven't seen it yet and can't catch it on the tube, definately make it a blockbuster night.  reefrunner
A classic for sure - one of the best "dialogue" movies of all time.  Lemmon's character is definitely great - "Old Gill" from the Simpsons is based on this character.
"You see this watch? That watch cost more than your car. I made $970,000 last year. How much you make?" LOL
I've never seen it, but if it has Jack Lemmon in it... it's gotta be good!!!
